
[1]tranquillity

   TRANQUIL'LITY, n. [L. tranquillitas.] Quietness; a calm state; freedom
   from disturbance or agitation. We speak of the tranquillity of public
   affairs, of the state, of the world, the tranquillity of a retired
   life, the tranquillity of mind proceeding from conscious rectitude.
